Installation
============

Download
--------

```shell
$ bower install interact
$ npm install interact.js
```

Either:

* with [Bower](http://bower.io/)
* with [npm](https://www.npmjs.org/)
* manually from http://interactjs.io/#download

Link
----

```html
<script src="/path/to/interact.js"></script>
```

After downloading the file, add to your page's HTML a `<script>` tag who's
`src` attribute points to the file.

CDN
---

```html
<script src="//cdn.jsdelivr.net/interact.js/<%= data.site.current_version %>/interact.min.js"></script>
<!-- or -->
<script src="//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/interact.js/<%= data.site.current_version %>/interact.min.js"></script>
```

If you'd prefer to use the [jsDelivr](http://www.jsdelivr.com/#!interact.js) or
[cdnjs](https://cdnjs.com/libraries/interact.js) CDNs instead, simply add a
script tag pointing to one of:

- `//cdn.jsdelivr.net/interact.js/<%= data.site.current_version %>/interact.min.js`
- `//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/interact.js/<%= data.site.current_version %>/interact.min.js`

Module
------

`interact` is exposed as a CommonJS module, an AMD module, or a global object
depending on what the environment supports.

